Interface ClusterConfigurator

All Superinterfaces:
ServiceConfigurator
public interface ClusterConfigurator
extends ServiceConfigurator

    • withRequestRequirement

      ClusterConfigurator withRequestRequirement​(java.lang.String resource, java.lang.String quantity)
      Add a resource requirement at cluster level. The requests for memory are measured in bytes. You can express memory as a plain integer or as a fixed-point integer using one of these suffixes: E, P, T, G, M, K. You can also use the power-of-two equivalents: Ei, Pi, Ti, Gi, Mi, Ki. The requests for cpu are measured in cpu units and can be expressed in millicores i.e. 100m is the same as 0.1
      Parameters:
      resource - the resource to be added as requirement cpu or memory
      quantity - the quantity required for the resource
      Returns:
      this object

    • withLimitRequirement

    • withRestartVersion

      ClusterConfigurator withRestartVersion​(java.lang.String restartVersion)
      Tells the operator whether the customer wants to restart the server pods. The value can be any String and it can be defined on domain, cluster or server to restart the different pods. After the value is added, the corresponding pods will be terminated and created again. If customer modifies the value again after the pods were recreated, then the pods will again be terminated and recreated.
      Parameters:
      restartVersion - If present, every time this value is updated the operator will restart the required servers
      Returns:
      this object
      Since:
      2.0
